lm-franchises-that-refuse-to-die/">Horror Film Franchises That Refuse To Die</a></strong><span class="post_attribute center"><span class="post_detail_date">September 30, 2025</span> by <a href="https://crimereads.com/author/michaelwehunt/">Michael Wehunt</a></span></div></li><li><div class="post_circle_thumb"><a href="https://crimereads.com/on-writing-contemporary-mysteries-vs-historical/"><img class="lazy" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/plugins/lb-content-widgets/img/lazy-sq.png" data-src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/02/Miss-Fishers-Murder-Mysteries-150x150.jpg" alt=""></a></div><div class="text-container"><strong class="title"><a href="https://crimereads.com/on-writing-contemporary-mysteries-vs-historical/">On Writing Contemporary Mysteries vs. Historical Ones</a></strong><span class="post_attribute center"><span class="post_detail_date">September 30, 2025</span> by <a href="https://crimereads.com/author/sherrythomas/">Sherry Thomas</a></span></div></li><li><div class="post_circle_thumb"><a href="https://crimereads.com/crime-and-the-city-capri/"><img class="lazy" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/plugins/lb-content-widgets/img/lazy-sq.png" data-src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2025/09/20210825130212-capri-campania-gettyimages-637818296-1-150x150.jpg" alt=""></a></div><div class="text-container"><strong class="title"><a href="https://crimereads.com/crime-and-the-city-capri/">Crime and the City: Capri</a></strong><span class="post_attribute center"><span class="post_detail_date">September 29, 2025</span> by <a href="https://crimereads.com/author/paul-french/">Paul French</a></span></div></li></ul></li>
